<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key F but hymn centres on Gm (②m) - dark minor feel. 12-bar two-phrase form.
- ^F (F#) in melody = chromatic leading tone into Gm; harp holds Bb (Gm chord) diatonic.
- D in chord labels = non-diatonic raised 7th of Gm; harp uses Gm (②m) instead.
- Bb = ④, F = ①, Gm = ②m, Am/C = ③m/⑤. All diatonic.
- LH 4-note open voicings throughout. RH 2-note thirds/sixths.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH G2 pedal predominates, reflecting the Gm center of this hymn.
- RH D5-G5 frame repeated at every Gm measure for consistency.
- Bars 7, 11 use descending RH parallel sixths echoing the falling melody.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Two identical phrases (bars 1-6, 7-12). Second phrase builds slightly higher in RH.
- Penultimate bars 11-12 mirror 7-8 exactly for closure.
-->
